            }
          ],
          "output": {
            "state": "dressing prepared",
            "description": "The dressing is thick, syrupy, and combined with oil."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "sub2",
      "title": "Caramelize Macadamias",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "step2",
          "action": "To caramelize the macadamias, place them in a frying pan and dry-roast for a few minutes, stirring occasionally, until they are lightly coloured on all sides. Add the butter. When it has melted, add the sugar, salt, and chilli flakes. Stir constantly with a wooden spoon to coat the nuts in the sugar as it caramelizes. Watch carefully as it will only take 1–2 minutes and the sugar can burn quickly. Turn out onto a sheet of greaseproof paper. Cool the nuts, then roughly chop them.",
          "time": "10min",
          "tools": [
            "frying pan",
            "wooden spoon",
            "greaseproof paper"
          ],
          "inputs": [
            {
              "type": "ingredient",
              "ref": "ing1"
            },
            {
              "type": "ingredient",
              "ref": "ing2"
            },
            {
              "type": "ingredient",
              "ref": "ing3"
            },
            {
              "type": "ingredient",
              "ref": "ing4"
            }
          ],
          "output": {
            "state": "nuts caramelized",
            "description": "The macadamia nuts are caramelized and chopped."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "sub3",
      "title": "Assemble Slaw",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "step3",
          "action": "Place the shredded cabbages in a large mixing bowl with the rest of the salad ingredients, including the nuts from step2. Add the dressing from step1 and toss together. Taste and add more salt if needed, then serve.",
